Spotify Playlist Creator
This Python script allows users to create Spotify playlists based on various criteria such as artist, song, genre, or album.

Prerequisites
Before running the script, you need to:

Install Python (version 3.x)
Install the Spotipy library (pip install spotipy)
Have a Spotify account
Register your application on the Spotify Developer Dashboard to get your client ID and client secret.
Setup
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/spotify-playlist-creator.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd spotify-playlist-creator
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Set up environment variables for your Spotify client ID and client secret:

On Windows:

bash
Copy code
set SPOTIPY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
set SPOTIPY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
On macOS/Linux:

bash
Copy code
export SPOTIPY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
export SPOTIPY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
Replace your_client_id and your_client_secret with the values obtained from the Spotify Developer Dashboard.

Usage
Run the script and follow the prompts to create playlists:

IMPORTANT: 
replace the value of the username variable in the main function with your spotify username

bash
python playlist_creator.py
Options:
Create playlist from artist: Enter the name of an artist to create a playlist based on their top tracks and related artists' tracks.

Create playlist from song: Enter the name of a song and the artist's name to create a playlist based on similar tracks.

Create playlist from genre: Enter a genre to create a playlist with tracks from that genre.

Create playlist from album: Enter the name of an album and the artist's name to create a playlist with tracks from that album and related albums.

Exit: Quit the script.

